gomodel:SYNGO_4641  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1. Immunofluorescence and confocal microscopy showed Netrin-1 co-localized with PSD95 and VGLUT1 in mouse cultured cortical neurons at DIV21.\n\nnote; data resolution is not sufficient to pinpoint the subcellular localization to within pre/post-synapse (or both), hence the annotation against more general \"synapse\" term.\n\n\"To determine the proportion of synapses containing netrin-1 or DCC in vivo, we stained for netrin-1 and DCC in conjunction with presynaptic and postsynaptic markers in histological sections prepared from 21-d-old mouse (Fig. 1k,l). Staining for netrin-1 and DCC overlaps substantially with excitatory synapses. These findings indicate that readily detectable levels of netrin-1 and DCC are present at excitatory synapses in the rat and mouse cortex during the developmental period of synaptogenesis.\". Experimental description: \"For Fig. 1, k and l, P21 mouse brain was fixed by ...\"\n\nrat anti-netrin-1 (R&D Systems)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2022-05-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4641" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

